      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Zytglogge"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Perhaps the most iconic symbol in Bern is the Zytglogge, the giant beautiful clock tower in the middle of town. The ornate clock was put in place on the tower in 1530, but the tower itself was one of the first city gates of the city (built around the year 1200). Throughout the day, four minutes before each hour, figures come out and dance around."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/20160213_115758.jpg",
