                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/20160213_115758.jpg",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Barenpark"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Another iconic part of Bern is the bear pit in the middle of the city. The name Bern supposedly came from the word \"bear\", because the founder of Bern hunted a bear in the general location of today's city. The picture below shows the old bear pit where you can now go and read a little about the history of the bears. Since it was winter, the bears were hibernating, but we were able to see them through a camera in their hibernation rooms (see second picture below). They are so cute! Thankfully, today, they can roam free in a 65,000 square foot open air park whenever they are out of hibernation. I'd love to go back and see them out in the park!"
          }
        ]
      },
